[thinking] **Considering method retrieval**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I realize that methods might be declared in a superclass or interface instead of just in DefaultDriver. There's a chance that calling getDeclaredMethod on DefaultDriver could fail. It seems better to implement a method finder that traverses the class hierarchy and interfaces. Using direct reflection to find the method might be the most effective approach to ensure that I don't miss any relevant methods in the hierarchy.
